when ever you want to crack the kali linux password :

when you start kali , two option will come up :
 
 1 > Kali GNU/Linux
 2 > Advanced options for Kali GNU/Linux
 
 select the first option and press ' e ' and new menue will be appeared
 
 go an the ' linux ' option under ' echo ' 
 
 coming on ' linux '  come on ' ro ' and change it into ' rw ' and after ' splash ' type  ' init=/bin/bash ' and press ' F10 '
 
 now a terminal will be appeared now type ' passwd username ' and reset the password.
 
 VOILA!! you cracked the kali linux password.
